DataElement.preferredName: Number Cell Per Milliliter Total 2 Decimal Place Count
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the number of cells in a milliter of liquid.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A numeral or string of numerals expressing value, quantity, or identification._The smallest units of living structure capable of independent existence, composed of a membrane-enclosed mass of protoplasm and containing a nucleus or nucleoid._For each, generally denoting a ratio.__A measure of volume for a liquid.  A milliliter is approximately 950 times smaller than a quart and 30 times smaller than a fluid ounce.  A milliliter of liquid and a cubic centimeter (cc) of liquid are the same.
